The Federal Government has declared Tuesday, July 20 and Wednesday, July 21, 2021, as public holidays to mark this yearâ€™s Eid-el-Kabir celebration. Interior Minister Rauf Aregbesola made the declaration on Thursday on behalf of the Federal Government. He congratulated Muslims in Nigeria and across the world on the celebration. A statement in Abuja by the Permanent Secretary in the ministry, Dr. Shuaib Belgore, urged Nigerians to observe COVID-19 protocols during the celebration.